text: Hi McCall. Thanks for replying to my tweets. I hope you and your family have a great weekend.
@bobkevoian Hi Bob. I hope you teach Lucky when he meets Mr. McGee to say Chiiiiiiiccccckkkk! I miss not hearing you say that.
How lucky is Lucky to have grandparents like you to teach him the finer points of life and baseball.
Your Dad would be proud of how you cheer on the Dodger Blue.
Raining hard here in Springfield,Ohio.the Dish TV just went out. Trying to listen to WS pre-game on radio. Is this the 1940’s!
I went to a Dodgers vs Cincinnati game at Crossley field. Don Drysdsle pitched. He hit a game winning HR. Saw Sandy Koufax. Great memory.
Hopefully the camera will not show that guy picking his nose again. It looked like he was digging for home.
A big sixth inning. You can put your pants back on. Underwear is optional.
Happy Halloween to a great lady. Enjoy Lynne.
I wonder if your neighbor, Pat will be giving the kids beer for trick or treat?
What a heartbreaker! She sure is a cute little lamb.
@bonewheel3000 Hi Brad. Is Elaine OK?
As a retiree, I find pants now to be annoying. I just use my suspenders to hold my socks up.
Our leaves are still green on most of our trees still. I hope they fall soon before the first measurable snow fall.
What is the target age for the book series? I may order them for my Granddaughter.
Hi Tara. I like your weather broadcasts. Lucia is a beautiful baby. I enjoyed Katie’s segments on Living Dayton. Best wishes.
Last year you broadcasted from Young’s Jersey Dairy. Hope you do that again.
That ball got out of there like itt was covered with Astroglide!
I am watching a reality car show but now you have my attention.
#BobbleedsDodgerblue
